body.description: No job is too big, no pup is too small! Luvs diapers with new Paw Patrol designs have your back—and their butts. Luvs now has up to 12 hours of protection, day and night. Like Chase and Marshall would say, our highly trained paws are at your service. And diaper leaks? We’re on the case with nonstop leak protection. Luvs Triple Leakguards absorb quickly to help stop diaper leaks before they happen. But our leak protection doesn’t stop there. Secure cuffs and stretchy sides keep leaks locked in where they happen the most. Forget about cheap, leaky diapers and spend more time enjoying this ride known as parenting. With Luvs you know when they go, thanks to a wetness indicator that turns blue on contact with wetness. You care what your baby wears, so Luvs diapers are 100% hypoallergenic, made free of parabens and free of latex* (*natural rubber). When it comes to the ultimate diaper protection, these paws uphold the laws. Our diapers are so good, you don’t need this, but Luvs does offer a money-back guarantee. If you aren’t fully loving your Luvs diapers, we will gladly send you a refund. See luvsdiapers.com for terms and conditions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome for sensitive skin
reviews.reviewText: My baby does great with these, she seems to have allergic reactions to all the other ones I buy even the “natural” kinds, she will break out into a bad rash quickly because of her eczema. So these are very gentle for her skin. I also like that the big box isn’t a character design instead they have cheeky little quotes “these rolls are homemade” “I woke up like this” they’re too cute. These are super affordable, I can get an entire box worth and the average to about 17 cents per diaper, she’s exclusively breastfed and goes through many diapers a day so it really helps to have a lot of diapers on hand and make less trips to the store. A tip for all diapers, size up to avoid blowouts, if my baby has more than three blowouts in a week I size up, I like them to fit just over the belly button and high on the back....I’m not sure why others take stars off because they’d prefer their children to be sitting in a dirty diaper for 4+ hours on end, diapers should changed as often as a child needs to relieve themselves not when the diaper is at max capacity of urine and feces.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These luv diapers are good for daytime, however, wouldn't trust them for night time. It does not tend to hold much and that's why I only use them when I know I will be home to change my baby. If you want something absorbent, this is not it, however, it does get the work done. I downgraded from huggies and pampers since they were a bit expensive but only use those for night time as they are very absorbent. If you are worried about leakage these diapers probably won't work.
